sor Marston�� tells the story of the man who created Wonder Woman and the women who inspired him both in and out of bed. The movie gleams and has all the smooth surfaces and persuasive detail of a typical period picture ��� the fedoras the rides the Katharine Hepburn trousers. All that luster which too often in movies suggests polite manners and drowsily safe entertainment proves to be a seductive glossy way into something more satisfyingly complicated." life has already become interesting for Marston. The writer-director Angela Robinson lays out just how well knotty it all is with wit sympathy and economy. Spanning decades the story takes flight in 1928 with Marston teaching young lovelies at Radcliffe. ���Are you normal?�� he asks of a beaming receptive audience that serves as an amusing stand-in for the viewer. Marston has answers to that and other questions along with a theory he calls DISC ��� for dominance inducement submission and compliance ��� which sounds terribly complex and slightly ridiculous. (���D I S and C �� the real Marston wrote ���represent nodal points in the integrative emotion series.��)" 
