han a dutiful trip back to the pop-culture fairy-tale well. Its classicism feels unforced and fresh. Its romance neither winks nor panders. It looks good moves gracefully and leaves a clean and invigorating aftertaste. I almost didn��t recognize the flavor: I think the name for it is joy." Belle a bookish and ingenious young woman who lives with her father (Kevin Kline) in a picture-book French village." 
