ctly detailed as those of their counterparts in some of this movie��s Oscar rivals but they are enigmatic and individual in ways that are hard to forget." a bit of caution may be in order for parents. While nothing shown onscreen is graphic or disturbing the movie is frank about the way the characters have been treated and also about their natural curiosity regarding the adult world. Viewers who have read contemporary young-adult literature will be able to handle it though their parents may feel uncomfortable at times. Children of Zucchini��s age or younger might be freaked out." 
